The paper discusses authorship verification, which is a topic related to natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions digital text forensics, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The evaluation of the AV methods involves the use of corpora, which suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses classification algorithms, which is a topic related to machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
